Name: WHS-PRO-041 F-03 Construction Switchboard and Wiring Checklist - 6 Monthly
Prompting Name: WHS-PRO-041 F-03 Construction Switchboard and Wiring Checklist - 6 Monthly

Name: Construction Switchboards complete ALL check points, Load Centres (lunch shed, site offices etc.) complete noted check points only.
All electrical equipment and lighting/ power supplied from a 30mA RCBO
Readily accessible, i.e. not obstructed in any way
Robust construction with a minimum IP23 rating
Complete operational checks of all RCD’s i.e. push the test button
Spider boards are not exposed to the weather
Live components are effectively protected (check pole fillers)
Insulated Tie bar has been fitted for flexible cords
Switchboard/ Load centre door is lockable, non-removable without a tool and fitted with a retention device to stay in the open position
Mounting is secure and stable including secured to the floor
Where there is more than one breaker, marking provided by means of number, letters or both to distinguish one from the other (unique ID)
Marked with appropriate signage such as “danger 240V / 415V”, “lightning bolt”, “source of supply is identified” and” Keep Closed- Run all leads through the bottom”.
Main isolator installed capable of isolating all downstream circuits, is labelled appropriately i.e. MAIN SWITCH and is capable of being locked or within a lockable space.
Visual indicator of periodic test, i.e. current test tag installed
Confirm wiring is not tied or bundled with permanent wiring system
Marker tape (yellow “construction wiring”) installed at intervals not exceeding 5 meters (unless cable is readily distinguishable colour from permanent installation)
Permanent wiring in vicinity to be marked “live wiring”
Mechanical protection installed as required including the use of plain screw adaptors (glands are not to be used)
Visually inspect each circuit or sub mains entire route length to verify integrity of the installation as is practicable and safe.
Adequate access lighting provided, minimum 40 lux
Emergency lighting (when required) adequate for safe egress – minimum 20 lux average
Emergency Lighting Register complete, site plan marked up accordingly
Visually inspect each circuit entire route length to verify integrity of the installation as practicable
Emergency Lighting Battery Test – to be completed every six months
